    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Water-soluble and alcohol-soluble protein obtained from egg, blood, or milk; used in adhesives, finishes, coatings, varnish, as a clarifying agent for tannin, and in oil emulsion. The spelling with "i" is typically reserved fro this broader meaning. Use "albumen (egg white)" (spelled with an "e") for egg-white protein in the context of food preparation or photography.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000027671/Brady and Clauser, Materials Handbook (1977)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047822/MFA Conservation and Art Material Encyclopedia Online: CAMEO (2005-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Proteína soluble en agua y en alcohol obtenida de la sangre, huevos o leche, utilizada en adhesivos, terminaciones, revestimientos, barnices y como agente clarificador para el tanino y emulsiones en aceite.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een proteïne die oplost in water en alcohol en wordt verkregen uit bloed, ei of melk; wordt gebruikt in hechtmiddelen, lakken, beschermlagen en vernis en als een zuiveringsmiddel voor looizuur en emulsies in olie.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052374/Polytechnisch woordenboek En-Ne (1991)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099099/Van Dale groot woordenboek (1994)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種可溶於水及酒精的蛋白質，取自血液、蛋或牛奶。可用於膠黏劑、末道漆、塗層、亮光漆，也可做為鞣質及油狀乳液的澄清劑。蛋白素原文若拼為「albumin」（內含字母i），通常意指較廣義的蛋白素；當拼為「albumen」（內含字母e）時，則常特指蛋白的蛋白素，尤其是在攝影及其它藝術情境下。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
